FBIS4-10774 "drlat073_m_94013" FBIS-LAT-94-073 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 Brazil New Presidential Spokesman Named New Presidential Spokesman Named PY1504002894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1653 GMT 13 Apr 94 PY1504002894 Madrid EFE Spanish BFN [Text] Brasilia, 13 Apr (EFE) -- The Planalto Palace Press Office reported that Brazilian President Itamar Franco today appointed journalist Fernando Jose da Costa as the new presidential spokesman, replacing Francisco Baker. Da Costa is a 58-year-old employee of the state-owned radio and television network Radiobras [Brazilian Radio Broadcasting Company]. He has served as deputy to Baker for the past 18 months since Franco's inauguration. Baker resigned as Franco's spokesman last month to take a top position in communications at the IMF in Washington.
